1 Section 1. Section 2-958, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement,
2 2024, is amended to read:
3 2-958 (1) A noxious weed control fund may be established for each
4 control authority, which fund shall be available for expenses authorized
5 to be paid from such fund, including necessary expenses of the control
6 authority in carrying out its duties and responsibilities under the
7 Noxious Weed Control Act. The weed control superintendent within the
8 county shall (a) ascertain and tabulate each year the approximate amount
9 of land infested with noxious weeds and its location in the county, (b)
10 ascertain and prepare all information required by the county board in the
11 preparation of the county budget, including actual and expected revenue
12 from all sources, cash balances, expenditures, amounts proposed to be
13 expended during the year, and working capital, and (c) transmit such
14 information tabulated by the control authority to the county board not
15 later than June 1 of each year.
16 (2) The Noxious Weed Cash Fund is created. The fund shall consist of
17 proceeds raised from fees imposed for the registration of pesticides and
18 earmarked for the fund pursuant to section 2-2634, funds credited or
19 transferred pursuant to sections 2-509, 2-518, and 81-201, and 81-201.05,
20 any gifts, grants, or donations from any source, and any reimbursement
21 funds for control work done pursuant to subdivision (1)(b)(vi) of section
22 2-954. An amount from the General Fund may be appropriated annually for
23 the Noxious Weed Control Act. The fund shall be administered and used by
24 the director to maintain the noxious weed control program and for
25 expenses directly related to the program. Until January 1, 2025, the fund
26 may also be used to defray all reasonable and necessary costs related to
27 the administration of the Nebraska Hemp Farming Act.
28 (3) Any money in the fund available for investment shall be invested
29 by the state investment officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital
30 Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment Act.
31 Sec. 2. Section 2-1091, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
-3-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 amended to read:
2 2-1091 For the purpose of implementation or enforcement of the Plant
3 Protection and Plant Pest Act or any rule or regulation, the department
4 may:
5 (1) Enter at reasonable times and in a reasonable manner without
6 being subject to any action for trespass or damages, if reasonable care
7 is exercised, all property where plants are grown, packed, held prior to
8 distribution, or distributed for the purpose of inspecting all plants,
9 structures, vehicles, equipment, packing materials, containers, records,
10 and labels on such property or otherwise implementing or enforcing the
11 act. The department may inspect and examine all records and property
12 relating to compliance with the act. Such records and property shall be
13 made available to the department for review at all reasonable times;
14 (2) In a reasonable manner, hold for inspection and take samples of
15 any plants and associated materials which may not be in compliance with
16 the act;
17 (3) Inspect or reinspect at any time or place any plants that are in
18 the state or being shipped into or through the state and treat, seize,
19 destroy, require treatment or destruction of, or return to the state of
20 origin any plants in order to inhibit or prevent the movement of plant
21 pests throughout the state;
22 (4) Obtain an inspection warrant in the manner prescribed in
23 sections 29-830 to 29-835 from a court of record if any person refuses to
24 allow the department to inspect pursuant to this section;
25 (5) Issue a written or printed withdrawal-from-distribution order
26 and post signs to delineate sections not marked pursuant to subsection
27 (3) of section 2-1095 or sections of distribution locations and to notify
28 persons of any withdrawal-from-distribution order when the department has
29 reasonable cause to believe any lot of nursery stock is being distributed
30 in violation of the act or any rule or regulation;
31 (6) Apply for a restraining order, a temporary or permanent
-4-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 injunction, or a mandatory injunction against any person violating or
2 threatening to violate the act or the rules and regulations. The district
3 court of the county where the violation is occurring or is about to occur
4 shall have jurisdiction to grant such relief upon good cause shown.
5 Relief may be granted notwithstanding the existence of any other remedy
6 at law and shall be granted without bond;
7 (7) Issue a quarantine or establish a quarantine area;
8 (8) Cooperate and enter into agreements, including harmonization
9 plans, with any person in order to carry out the purpose of the act;
10 (9) Establish a restricted plant pest list to prohibit the movement
11 into the state of plant pests not known to occur in Nebraska and to
12 prohibit the movement of those plant pests present in the state but known
13 to be destructive to the plant industry;
14 (10) Issue European corn borer quarantine certificates,
15 phytosanitary certificates, and export certificates on plants for
16 individual shipment to other states or foreign countries if those plants
17 comply with the requirements or regulations of such state or foreign
18 country or issue quarantine compliance agreements or European corn borer
19 quarantine certification licenses;
20 (11) Inspect plants that any person desires to ship into another
21 state or country when such person has made an application to the
22 department for such inspection. The inspection shall determine the
23 presence of plant pests to determine the acceptance of the plants into
24 other states or countries. The department may accept the inspections of
25 laboratories authorized by the department or field inspectors of the
26 department;
27 (12) Certify plants or property to meet the requirements of specific
28 quarantines imposed on Nebraska or Nebraska plants. The quarantine
29 certification requirements shall be set forth in the rules and
30 regulations;
31 (13) Assess Until increased or decreased by rules or regulations,
