1 sections of all growing areas. A section shall be not larger than five
2 acres.
3 (4) All growing areas within the state shall be inspected by the
4 department at least once per year for certification and compliance with
5 the Plant Protection and Plant Pest Act.
6 (5) Following the certification inspection of Nebraska-grown nursery
7 stock, the department shall provide a copy of the plant inspection report
8 to the nursery stock distributor specifying any area of the nursery from
9 which nursery stock cannot be distributed or any plants which may not be
10 distributed as nursery stock. When deemed necessary to maintain
11 compliance with the purposes of the Plant Protection and Plant Pest Act,
12 the department shall require the nursery stock distributor to withdraw
13 from distribution any variety or amount of nursery stock. A reinspection
14 may be conducted by the department at the nursery stock distributor's
15 request and cost. The department may also reinspect to determine
16 compliance with the act. To determine the cost of any reinspection, the
17 department shall use fees as outlined in subsection (2) of this section.
18 The nursery stock distributor shall comply with the recommendations of
19 the department as to the treatment or destruction of nursery stock.
20 (6) The department may require the treatment or destruction of any
21 nursery stock that is infested or infected with plant pests, nonviable,
22 damaged, or desiccated to the point of not being reasonably capable of
23 growth.
24 (7) Any nursery stock on which a withdrawal-from-distribution order
25 has been issued shall be released for distribution only by authorized
26 department employees or after written permission has been obtained from
27 the department. Each nursery stock distributor shall promptly report to
28 the department, in writing, the amount and type of plants treated or
29 destroyed under requirements on withdrawal-from-distribution orders. The
30 department may withhold a license or certification of Nebraska-grown
31 nursery stock until conditions have been met by the nursery stock
-11-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 distributor as specified in the plant inspection report or any other
2 order issued by the department. A certification of Nebraska-grown stock
3 may be issued covering portions of the nursery which are not infested or
4 infected if the nursery stock distributor agrees to treat, destroy, or
5 remove as specified by the department those plants found to be infested
6 or infected.
7 Sec. 5. Section 2-10,117, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, is
8 amended to read:
9 2-10,117 All money received from any source pursuant to the Plant
10 Protection and Plant Pest Act shall be remitted by the department to the
11 State Treasurer and by the State Treasurer credited to the Plant
12 Protection and Plant Pest Cash Fund which is hereby created. The fund
13 also shall include funds transferred pursuant to section 81-201.05. The
14 fund shall be used by the department to aid in defraying the expenses of
15 administering the act. Any money in the fund available for investment
16 shall be invested by the state investment officer pursuant to the
17 Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska State Funds Investment
18 Act. The State Treasurer shall transfer any money in the Nebraska Potato
19 Development Fund upon the termination of such fund to the Plant
20 Protection and Plant Pest Cash Fund.
