10 Sec. 10. Section 49-1499.02, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
11 is amended to read:
12 49-1499.02 (1) An official or employee of the executive branch of
13 state government who would be required to take any action or make any
14 decision in the discharge of his or her official duties that may cause
15 financial benefit or detriment to him or her, a member of his or her
16 immediate family, or a business with which he or she is associated, which
17 is distinguishable from the effects of such action on the public
18 generally or a broad segment of the public, shall take the following
19 actions as soon as he or she is aware of such potential conflict or
20 should reasonably be aware of such potential conflict, whichever is
21 sooner:
22 (a) Prepare a written statement describing the matter requiring
23 action or decision and the nature of the potential conflict; and
24 (b) Deliver a copy of the statement to the commission and to his or
25 her immediate superior, if any, who shall assign the matter to another.
26 If the immediate superior does not assign the matter to another or if
27 there is no immediate superior, the official or employee shall take such
28 action as the commission shall advise or prescribe to remove himself or
29 herself from influence over the action or decision on the matter.
30 (2) This section does not prevent such a person from (a) making or
31 participating in the making of a governmental decision to the extent that
-15-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 the individual's participation is legally required for the action or
2 decision to be made or (b) making or participating in the making of a
3 governmental decision if the potential conflict of interest is based upon
4 a business association and the business association exists only as the
5 result of his or her position on a commodity board. A person acting
6 pursuant to subdivision (a) of this subsection shall report the
7 occurrence to the commission.
8 (3) For purposes of this section, commodity board means only the
9 following:
10 (a) Corn Development, Utilization, and Marketing Board;
