28 Sec. 33. Section 81-2,162.27, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
29 is amended to read:
30 81-2,162.27 (1) All money received under the Nebraska Commercial
31 Fertilizer and Beneficial Substances Soil Conditioner Act and the
-34-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 Agricultural Liming Materials Act shall be remitted to the State
2 Treasurer for credit to the Fertilizers and Beneficial Substances Soil
3 Conditioners Administrative Fund.
4 (2) The Fertilizers and Beneficial Substances Administrative Fund ,
5 which fund is hereby created. Money in the fund so received shall be used
6 by the department for defraying the expenses of administering the
7 Nebraska Commercial Fertilizer and Beneficial Substances Soil Conditioner
8 Act, and the Agricultural Liming Materials Act, and any other plant
9 health program that is administered by the department. The fund may also
10 be used to defray costs incurred by the department directly related to
11 administrative and budgetary support of the Healthy Soils Task Force
12 pursuant to sections 2-401 to 2-404, except that no more than ten
13 thousand dollars may be expended by the department from the fund for such
14 purpose. Transfers may be made from the fund to the General Fund at the
15 direction of the Legislature. The State Treasurer shall transfer two
16 hundred seventy-five thousand dollars from the Fertilizers and Soil
17 Conditioners Administrative Fund to the General Fund on or before June
18 30, 2019, on such dates and in such amounts as directed by the budget
19 administrator of the budget division of the Department of Administrative
20 Services.
21 (3) (2) Any unexpended balance in the Fertilizers and Beneficial
22 Substances Soil Conditioners Administrative Fund at the close of any
23 biennium shall, when reappropriated, be available for the uses and
24 purposes of the fund for the succeeding biennium. Any money in the fund
25 available for investment shall be invested by the state investment
26 officer pursuant to the Nebraska Capital Expansion Act and the Nebraska
27 State Funds Investment Act.
28 Sec. 34. Section 81-2,162.28, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska,
29 is amended to read:
30 81-2,162.28 The Nebraska Commercial Fertilizer and Beneficial
31 Substances Soil Conditioner Act and any rules and regulations adopted and
-35-

LB948 LB948
2026 2026
1 promulgated thereunder shall supersede and preempt any ordinance, rule,
2 regulation, or resolution enacted by any political subdivision of the
3 state regarding the regulation of any fertilizer or beneficial substance
4 and soil conditioners. No political subdivision shall prohibit or in any
5 other manner regulate any matter relating to the registration, labeling,
6 or sale of any fertilizer or beneficial substance and soil conditioners.
7 No political subdivision shall prohibit or in any other manner regulate
8 any matter relating to the storage, transportation, distribution,
9 notification of use, or use that is in addition to or in conflict with
10 the Nebraska Commercial Fertilizer and Beneficial Substances Soil
11 Conditioner Act and any rules and regulations adopted and promulgated
12 thereunder. Nothing in this section shall be construed to preempt or
13 otherwise limit the authority of any city or county to adopt and enforce
14 zoning regulations or any natural resources district to enforce the
15 Nebraska Ground Water Management and Protection Act.
16 Sec. 35. Original sections 2-1091, 2-1091.02, 2-1095, 2-10,117,
17 2-2634, 2-3401, 2-4323, 2-4324, 49-1499.02, 81-201, 81-2,162.01,
18 81-2,162.02, 81-2,162.03, 81-2,162.04, 81-2,162.05, 81-2,162.06,
19 81-2,162.07, 81-2,162.11, 81-2,162.12, 81-2,162.13, 81-2,162.14,
20 81-2,162.15, 81-2,162.16, 81-2,162.17, 81-2,162.18, 81-2,162.20,
21 81-2,162.21, 81-2,162.22, 81-2,162.23, 81-2,162.25, 81-2,162.26,
22 81-2,162.27, and 81-2,162.28, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska, and
23 section 2-958, Revised Statutes Cumulative Supplement, 2024, are
24 repealed.
25 Sec. 36. The following sections are outright repealed: Sections
26 2-2801, 2-2802, 2-2803, 2-2804, 2-2805, 2-2806, 2-2807, 2-2809, 2-2810,
27 2-2811, 2-2812, and 81-201.05, Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska.
28 Sec. 37. Since an emergency exists, this act takes effect when
29 passed and approved according to law.
